  "local_port": 48180,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I get a job in Infosys off campus?",
  "response": "Securing a job at Infosys through off-campus recruitment requires a strategic approach. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Build a Strong Resume**\n   - **Highlight Relevant Skills**: Mention technical skills (programming languages, databases, etc.) and domain knowledge.\n   - **Showcase Projects**: Include academic or personal projects, internships, or certifications.\n   - **Tailor Your Resume**: Customize it to align with Infosys\u2019 job requirements.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Learn the Required Skills**\n   - **Technical Skills**: Focus on programming languages like Java, Python, SQL, and basics of data structures and algorithms.\n   - **Problem-Solving**: Practice logical reasoning and analytical thinking.\n   - **Communication Skills**: Work on verbal and written communication, as Infosys values soft skills.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Prepare for the Infosys Hiring Process**\n   - **Aptitude Test**: Practice quantitative aptitude, logical reasoning, and verbal ability questions.\n   - **Programming Test**: Be prepared to solve coding problems (pseudocode or programming languages).\n   - **Interview Preparation**:\n     - **Technical Round**: Be ready for questions on programming, databases, and basic computer science concepts.\n     - **HR Round**: Practice answering questions about your background, career goals, and how you align with Infosys\u2019 values.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Explore Off-Campus Opportunities**\n   - **Infosys Website**: Regularly check the [Infosys Careers](https://www.infosys.com/careers.html) page for openings.\n   - **Job Portals**: Use platforms like LinkedIn, Naukri, Indeed, and Glassdoor to find job postings.\n   - **Referrals**: Connect with Infosys employees on LinkedIn and request a referral.\n   - **Hackathons and Competitions**: Participate in coding competitions or hackathons sponsored by Infosys.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Stay Updated**\n   - Follow Infosys\u2019 social media profiles and career pages for updates on recruitment drives or walk-in interviews.\n   - Join forums and communities like Reddit or Telegram groups for job notifications.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Certifications (Optional but Recommended)**\n   - Complete certifications in relevant technologies (e.g., AWS, Azure, Python, Java) to strengthen your profile.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Apply Strategically**\n   - Apply for entry-level positions like Systems Engineer or Associate Consultant.\n   - Ensure your application is error-free and highlights your strengths.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Be Persistent and Positive**\n   - Off-campus recruitment can take time, so stay consistent and keep improving your skills.\n\nBy following these steps and staying proactive, you can increase your chances of landing a job at Infosys. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
